<h1>TSMMIS MATLAB Project Report</h1>
<p class="center"><b>Self-Supervised Few-Shot Steel Surface Defect Recognition</b></p>
<p class="center small">Project source: <code>D:\MVRP_Project\TSMMIS_MATLAB</code></p>

<h2>1) Project Overview</h2>
<p>
This project implements a TSMMIS-style self-supervised few-shot pipeline for steel surface defect recognition on the
NEU-CLS dataset. The main execution script is <code>main_TSMMIS.m</code>, which runs data preparation, encoder initialization,
unlabeled feature pretraining, few-shot evaluation, and t-SNE visualization export.
</p>
<p>
The pipeline evaluates few-shot recognition for <b>1, 2, 3, and 4 labeled samples per class</b> with repeated randomized runs.
GPU is automatically used when available (<code>canUseGPU</code> in <code>main_TSMMIS.m</code>).
</p>

<h2>2) Dataset</h2>
<p>
Dataset path used by the project: <code>data\NEU-CLS</code>. The project uses 6 classes:
<b>cra, in, pa, ps, rs, sc</b> (Crazing, Inclusion, Patches, Pitted Surface, Rolled-in Scale, Scratches).
</p>
<p>
Based on the project dataset files, there are <b>240 images per class</b> (1,440 total images).
The configured split in <code>main_TSMMIS.m</code> is <b>60% train / 40% test</b> (<code>trainRatio = 0.6</code>).
</p>

